The **Profiles **panel allows to view and edit existing profiles, and to create new ones.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

## 
> Note

Profiles can be associated with both Accounts and Companies. For more information, see:

- [Doxee Platform Settings - Accounts](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-accounts)

- [Doxee Platform Settings - Companies](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-companies)

## Managing profiles
### Creating a profile
- Click **Add**. The **Create Profile **form is displayed.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Enter the following details (mandatory fields are marked with an asterisk *):

**Section**

**Field**

**Mandatory**

**Description**

**General Information**

**Profile name**

X

Name of the profile (a combination of alphanumeric characters, spaces, and special characters)

**Scope**

X

Doxee Platform functionality to which the profiling refers. The possible options are:

**Option**

**Account**

**Company**

**Description**

**Batch Workflows**

X

Define which tasks can be used to design batch workflows.

**On-Demand Workflows**

X

Define which tasks can be used to design on-demand workflows.

**Electronic Invoicing**

X

Define company data that will be used to autofill the pre-configured fields in new invoices.

**Tags**

**Tags**

Enter one or more tags (up to 10 tags, separated by a comma) to label the profile. Tags may have a maximum length of 20 characters.

- Click **Save **to confirm.

### Viewing the details of a profile
Click on the name of a profile to view its details.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

For more information on how to edit a company, see [Editing a profile](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-profiles#editing-a-profile) below.

> Note

The **History **panel lists all changes performed on the profile, including the status icon, date and time, and name of the user who performed the action.

### Editing a profile
- Click on the name of a profile to view its details.

or:

Select the profile that you want to modify and click **Edit**.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Edit the required information.

> Note

For more information on the available fields, see [Creating a profile](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-profiles#creating-a-profile) above.

- Click **Update **to confirm.

> Tip

If you make any changes to the profile details and then click on a different tab or the **Back **browser button, the system displays the following prompt, allowing you to save, discard, or cancel the changes.
